\layout Standard


\begin_inset Formula \begin{equation}
\T'_{n}(x)=\begin{cases}
2x\sum\limits _{k=0}^{n/2}kc_{k}x^{2(k-1)}, & n=0,2,4,\ldots\\
\sum\limits _{k=0}^{(n-1)/2}(2k+1)c_{k}x^{2k}, & n=1,3,5,\ldots\end{cases}\label{eq:chebyt_diff_explicit}\end{equation}

\end_inset 

 
\layout Standard

Ähnlich wie 
\begin_inset Formula $\T_{n}$
\end_inset 

